          <title>Stars forward Mason Marchment taken to hospital after getting hit in face by puck</title>
          <description><![CDATA[DALLAS (AP) — Stars forward Mason Marchment was helped off the ice during Friday night’s game against the Minnesota Wild and taken to a hospital after being hit in the face by a puck. Dallas coach Pete DeBoer said Marchment is OK, but was not sure how long he’ll be sidelined.]]></description>
